==English==
===Etymology===
Formed as {{suffix|allocare|able}}, on model of {{la}} {{term|allocare|lang=la}}, rather than from {{en}} {{term|allocate|lang=en}}.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}
# Able to be [[allocated]]

====Usage notes====
The form {{term|allocatable|lang=en}} (regular English derivation from {{term|allocate|lang=en}}) is also found, but is primarily used in computing; in legal use the term is '''allocable'''.

